rain, to educate","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"المعلم يعلم الطلاب الرياضيات.","english":"The teacher teaches the students mathematics."},{"text":"إِنَّهُ لَكَبِيرُكُمُ الَّذِي عَلَّمَكُمُ السِّحْرَ فَلَسَوْفَ تَعْلَمُونَ","english":"He is indeed your chief who has taught you magic! Soon you will know!"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to designate, to mark, to earmark","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَلِمَ (ʕalima) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knowledge, learning, lore"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cognition, acquaintance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"information"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"perception, knowledge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"science","examples":[{"text":"الْعُلُوم","english":"the natural sciences"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sign, token, mark, badge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"harelip"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"road sign, guidepost"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flag, banner"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"authority, luminary, star, personage, distinguished man"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a mountain","examples":[{"text":"أَشْهَرُ مِنْ نَارٍ عَلَى عَلَم","english":"very famous"},{"text":"وَمِنْ آيَاتِهِ ٱلْجَوَارِ فِي ٱلْبَحْرِ كَٱلْأَعْلَامِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"proper noun"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Classical Arabic form of عَالَم (ʕālam)","tags":["Arabic","Classical","alt-of"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.li.ma/","/ʕal.la.ma/","/ʕilm/","/ʕa.lam/","/ʕaː.lam/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30368","headword_ar":"اَعْلَمُ","root":"Elm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, knowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. Applied to God, [it may often be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Supreme in knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"omniscient:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but often, in this case,] it means [simply] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlimN","text_ar":"عَالِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cognizant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Jel in iii. 31, and I'Ak p. 240.) [Therefore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^aEolamu","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَعْلَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"virtually means, sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God knows best;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knows all things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes, simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God knows."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Harelipped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a fissure in his upper lip:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in one of its two sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the camel is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElm","text_ar":"اعلم"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the fissure in his upper lip: when the fissure is in the lower lip, the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolaHu","text_ar":"اَفْلَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oramu","text_ar":"اَشْرَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in both of these, and also in other, similar, senses: (TA:) the fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolamu","text_ar":"اَعْلَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalomaA='u","text_ar":"عَلْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, TA:) which is likewise applied to a lip ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afapN","text_ar":"شَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEalomaA='u","text_ar":"العَلْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The coat of mail:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) mentioned by Sh, in the book entitled"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbu Als~ilaAHi","text_ar":"كِتَابُ السِّلَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but as not heard by him except in a verse of Zuheyr Ibn-Khabbáb [?]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85/","headword_ar":"اعلم","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23805#76d72c","body_html":"<span>اعلم: أن نعم لتقرير الكلام السابق وتصديقه، موجبًا كان أو منفيًا، طلبًا كان أو خبرًا؛ من غير رفع وإبطال، ولهذا قالوا: إذا قيل في جواب قوله تعالى: {أَلَسْتُ بِرَبِّكُمْ} نعم، يكون كفرًا، وأما بلى فلنقض المتكلم المنفي لفظًا كان أم معنى، مع حرف الاستفهام ألا.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_22","lexicon_en":"Al-Munāwī, al-Tawqīf ʿalā Muhimmāt al-Taʿārīf (d. 1622 CE)","lexicon_ar":"التوقيف على مهمات التعاريف للمناوي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23805#76a09c","body_html":"<span>اعلم: حث للمخاطب على أن يلقي سمعه إلى ما يعقبها وهو شهيد ذكره الشريف. </span><br>"}]}}